23/02/2011
BERLIN, Germany -- Chancellor Angela Merkel met with Greek Prime Minister George Papandreou in Berlin on Tuesday (February 22nd) suggesting afterwards that the EU may discuss extending the repayment period of Greece's bailout agreement. 
Athens received the three-year 110 billion-euro package last May amid its financial crisis. 
Papandreou reiterated his government's determination to continue reforms in different sectors, vowing "My country will not be a burden on German taxpayers ... 
We will pay back this bailout with interest." (Xinhua, Kathimerini - 22/02/11)
